Authentication

What it is: Verifying who the user is.

Purpose: Confirms identity (are you really you?).

How: Usually done via username & password, OTP, biometrics, etc.

Example: Logging into Gmail by entering your email and password.

Authorization

What it is: Determining what the user can do.

Purpose: Decides what resources or actions an authenticated user is allowed to access.

How: Based on roles/permissions (e.g., Admin, User, Guest).

Example: After logging in to Gmail, only you can view your inbox, but you cannot access someone elseâ€™s inbox.